      <a href="index.html?p=1501#comment-6134"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-04-05T04:52:00-04:00">Thursday, April 5, 2007 at 4:52 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I don&#8217;t know what kind of coconut pie you&#8217;re looking for, but just in case this might help you, have you ever tried Filipino buco pie?  It&#8217;s made with young coconut and is heavenly.  Of course you&#8217;ll have to travel to the Philippines to eat &#8220;the real thing&#8221;, but <>buco<> (young coconut) is available frozen here in the US, and makes a lovely pie &#8212; the texture will be different (buco pie in the Phils. is usually made with large pieces, almost sheets of the young coconut meat, here you can only get it shredded, or at least where I am), but I think if you&#8217;re looking for a coconut pie to love, it&#8217;s definitely a must-try.</></>oh, and loved the video btw.  i don&#8217;t comment here much but i&#8217;ve always admired your writing and was touched by your and B&#8217;s story.</p>
    </div>

